<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Crypto API Introduction</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
        }
        h2 {
            color: #34495e;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        code {
            background-color: #e8e8e8;
            padding: 2px 4px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-family: monospace;
        }
        .endpoint {
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 0.9em;
            color: #888;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to the Crypto API</h1>
        
        <h2>Endpoints</h2>
        
        <div class="endpoint">
            <p><strong>Get Transactions and Ethereum Price:</strong></p>
            <p>Navigate to: <code>/transaction/?address=SAMPLE_ADDRESS</code></p>
            <p>This endpoint returns a list of transactions for the specified address and the current Ethereum price.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="endpoint">
            <p><strong>Get Total Expenses and Ethereum Price:</strong></p>
            <p>Navigate to: <code>/totalExpense/?address=SAMPLE_ADDRESS</code></p>
            <p>This endpoint returns the total expenses for the specified address and the current Ethereum price.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Scheduler Setup</h2>
        <p>To ensure that the Ethereum price in the database is updated every 10 minutes, you need to run the following command on a separate server:</p>
        <pre><code>node priceUpdater.js</code></pre>
        
        <div class="footer">
            <p>&copy; 2024 Crypto API. All rights reserved.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
